RBS Chief Says ‘Macho’ Banking Culture Must Go, Telegraph Says

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-02-27T09:54:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/rbs-chief-says-macho-banking-culture-must-go-telegraph-says.html
The financial services sector must
eliminate its “macho” culture and help women rise to top
positions, Royal Bank of Scotland Plc Chairman Philip Hampton
said in an interview with the Sunday Telegraph.    Investment banking  in particular is a “male bastion” in
which it is difficult for women to obtain top jobs, the
newspaper cited Hampton as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
